{{Politics of Lithuania}}
A '''referendum on a new [[Constitution of Lithuania|constitution]]''' was held in [[Lithuania]] on 25 October 1992,<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1201 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> alongside the first round of [[Lithuanian parliamentary election, 1992|parliamentary elections]]. It was approved by 78.2% of those voting and 56.8% of all registered voters, passing the 50% threshold.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p1210</ref>
