A '''sejm court''' was a [[court]] that sat in cases of [[impeachment]] – in the words of the [[May 3 Constitution]] of 1791 (article VIII:  the judicial authority) – of government "[[Political minister|minister]]s [...] charged with breach of law by a deputation designated to examine their deeds [...]."

The composition and functioning of sejm courts were spelled out in an act of the Sejm passed on May 13, 1791.

